  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bahamas - Hurricane Dorian 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hurricane Dorian made landfall in the Bahamas on Sunday 1st September as a Category 5 hurricane. It was extremely slow moving with very strong winds (up to 185mph) heavy rainfall (35in) and significant storm surge (up to 4m) affecting the northern part of the country for a prolonged period of around 2 days. Abaco Island and Grand Bahama were the worst affected with extensive damage and destruction of buildings as well as damage to water transport and communications infrastructure. Initial estimate of 13 000 houses damaged or destroyed and upto 76 000 people affected. IFRC initially launched a DREF to support 2 500 people with 250k CHF but this was quickly followed by an appeal for 3.2m CHF to support 20 000.</narrative>
  </description>
